## Selector Scoring Rules (follow when evaluating scan results)

| Score | Strategy    | Example Selector                        | Use When                          |
|-------|-------------|-----------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| 100   | testId      | `[data-testid='login-btn']`             | `data-testid` / `data-cy` present |
| 90    | aria-label  | `[aria-label='Submit form']`            | `aria-label` attribute present    |
| 85    | id          | `#username`                             | Non-dynamic id present            |
| 80    | name        | `input[name='email']`                   | Form field with name attr         |
| 75    | placeholder | `input[placeholder='Enter email']`      | Input with placeholder            |
| 70    | type        | `input[type='password']`                | Specific input type               |
| 50    | class       | `button.submit-btn`                     | Stable, non-generated class       |
| 20    | xpath-text  | `//button[normalize-space()='Login']`   | Last resort — no other stable attr|

**Skip selectors** that look dynamic: long hex strings, auto-generated numbers (e.g. `#btn_29fk3`, `.css-1a2b3c`)

