## Important Rules

- **Always call `scan_page_selectors` first** before generating any code — never guess selectors
- **Never hardcode URLs** in step definitions — URL belongs in the POM `navigateTo()` method or a config file
- **One POM class per page** — don't mix selectors from different pages
- **Keep steps reusable** — `"the user clicks the login button"` is better than `"the user clicks the blue button at bottom"`
- **If page scan fails** (timeout / auth wall) — tell the user and ask if they want to provide HTML manually
- **If a selector scores below 30** — flag it with a comment: `// ⚠ low-confidence selector — verify manually`

